<paragraph id="2253A5512B21FFC0FD13FE3EFB5F9EF5" blockId="45.[732,1155,406,432]" box="[732,1155,406,432]" pageId="45" pageNumber="0">
<heading id="791B123D2B21FFC0FD13FE3EFB5F9EF5" box="[732,1155,406,432]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="45" pageNumber="0" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="E5ECDED22B21FFC0FD13FE3EFC369EF5" baseAuthorityName="de Saussure &amp; Zehntner" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[732,1002,406,432]" class="Diplopoda" family="Arthrosphaeridae" genus="Zoosphaerium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="45" pageNumber="0" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platylabum">
<emphasis id="109879432B21FFC0FD13FE3EFC369EF5" box="[732,1002,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="0">Zoosphaerium platylabum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2253A5512B21FFC0FD6AFE78FC1E9D44" blockId="45.[677,1209,463,513]" pageId="45" pageNumber="0">
SPECIES INCLUDED. — 
<taxonomicName id="E5ECDED22B21FFC0FC5EFE67FC629D44" authority="(de Saussure &amp; Zehntner, 1897)" baseAuthorityName="de Saussure &amp; Zehntner" baseAuthorityYear="1897" class="Diplopoda" family="Arthrosphaeridae" genus="Zoosphaerium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="45" pageNumber="0" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platylabum">
<emphasis id="109879432B21FFC0FC5EFE67FB4D9EA2" box="[913,1169,463,487]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="0">Zoosphaerium platylabum</emphasis>
(de 
<bibRefCitation id="467DD8A02B21FFC0FD6AFE41FC6A9D44" author="SAUSSURE H. &amp; DE &amp; ZEHNTNER L." box="[677,950,489,513]" pageId="45" pageNumber="0" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref39337" refString="SAUSSURE H. DE &amp; ZEHNTNER L. 1897. - Atlas de l'histoire naturelle des myriapodes, in GRANDIDIER A., Histoire physique, naturelle et politique de Madagascar 27 (3): pls 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1897">Saussure &amp; Zehntner, 1897</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6AF6F6DA2B21FFC0FD6AFDB1FCFE9D0E" pageId="45" pageNumber="0" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2253A5512B21FFC0FD6AFDB1FCFE9D0E" blockId="45.[677,1209,537,587]" pageId="45" pageNumber="0">DISTRIBUTION. — Unclear, since most species are still undescribed.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6AF6F6DA2B21FFC0FD6AFDCCFBEA9CDB" pageId="45" pageNumber="0" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2253A5512B21FFC0FD6AFDCCFB4C9D8F" blockId="45.[677,1210,611,926]" pageId="45" pageNumber="0">
DIAGNOSIS. — This species group is still monotypic, but numerous undescribed species close to 
<taxonomicName id="E5ECDED22B21FFC0FBC4FDD6FB569DD0" baseAuthorityName="de Saussure &amp; Zehntner" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[1035,1162,637,661]" class="Diplopoda" family="Arthrosphaeridae" genus="Zoosphaerium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="45" pageNumber="0" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platylabum">
<emphasis id="109879432B21FFC0FBC4FDD6FB569DD0" box="[1035,1162,637,661]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="0">Z. platylabum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were discovered, justifying its establishment. The characters unifying this group are unique in 
<taxonomicName id="E5ECDED22B21FFC0FC20FD1AFB509D8F" authorityName="Brandt" authorityYear="1833" box="[1007,1164,690,714]" class="Diplopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="45" pageNumber="0" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Sphaerotheriida</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2253A5512B21FFC0FD74FD65FBEA9CDB" blockId="45.[677,1210,611,926]" pageId="45" pageNumber="0">
All species have 2 locking carinae on the ventral side of the anal shield. The carinae are located more closely to the laterotergites than towards the anal shield margin (
<figureCitation id="BAD7B9D42B21FFC0FD64FCB4FCDF9C71" box="[683,771,796,820]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="47.[113,124,1566,1583]" captionTargetBox="[126,1203,219,1525]" captionTargetId="figure-19@47.[113,1209,215,1529]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIG. 30. — Zoosphaerium platylabum (de Saussure &amp; Zehntner, 1897): A-E, K, L, holotype; A, habitus, body length 36 mm; B, C, coxa and prefemur of 1st right leg with 1st stigma-carrying plate; B, posterior view;C, anterior view; D, 9th left leg; E, closing ledges of anal shield, F, coxa of second left leg with vulva, posterior view (♀ MNHG); G, coxa of 2nd left leg with gonopore (BLF 7994); H-J, right anterior telopod (BLF 7994); H, anterior view; I, joints 2 and 3, posterior view; J, joints 2 and 3, inner view; K, L, last two joints of right posterior telopod; K, anterior view; L, posterior view. Abbreviations: 12T, 12th tergite; AS, anal shield; Cx, coxa; LT, laterotergite; St, stigma-carrying plate. Scale bars: B-L, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5391785" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5391785/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="0">Fig. 30E</figureCitation>
). The operculum of female vulva is protruding into 2, sharp edged processes. (
<figureCitation id="BAD7B9D42B21FFC0FC09FC9FFBC69C0A" box="[966,1050,823,847]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="47.[113,124,1566,1583]" captionTargetBox="[126,1203,219,1525]" captionTargetId="figure-19@47.[113,1209,215,1529]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIG. 30. — Zoosphaerium platylabum (de Saussure &amp; Zehntner, 1897): A-E, K, L, holotype; A, habitus, body length 36 mm; B, C, coxa and prefemur of 1st right leg with 1st stigma-carrying plate; B, posterior view;C, anterior view; D, 9th left leg; E, closing ledges of anal shield, F, coxa of second left leg with vulva, posterior view (♀ MNHG); G, coxa of 2nd left leg with gonopore (BLF 7994); H-J, right anterior telopod (BLF 7994); H, anterior view; I, joints 2 and 3, posterior view; J, joints 2 and 3, inner view; K, L, last two joints of right posterior telopod; K, anterior view; L, posterior view. Abbreviations: 12T, 12th tergite; AS, anal shield; Cx, coxa; LT, laterotergite; St, stigma-carrying plate. Scale bars: B-L, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5391785" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5391785/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="0">Fig. 30F</figureCitation>
). A phylogenetic analysis will be necessary to confirm if the 
<taxonomicName id="E5ECDED22B21FFC0FBD6FCF9FBA09C2C" baseAuthorityName="de Saussure &amp; Zehntner" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[1049,1148,849,873]" class="Diplopoda" family="Arthrosphaeridae" genus="Zoosphaerium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="45" pageNumber="0" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platylabum">
<emphasis id="109879432B21FFC0FBD6FCF9FBA09C2C" box="[1049,1148,849,873]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="0">platylabum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group represents a monophyletic group to be kept separately from the other Malagasy sphaerotheriids.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
